     {q:"Why might readers connect strongly with bildungsroman narratives?", options:["The themes of growth and self-discovery often resonate with universal human experiences","This type of narrative offers no emotional resonance for readers","These narratives have no connection to relatable human experiences","Readers never form a connection with coming-of-age stories"], answer:0},
     {q:"Which is an example of an event that might occur in a bildungsroman?", options:["A story with no meaningful character development at all","A plot that remains completely unchanged from beginning to end","The protagonist facing a significant challenge that changes their understanding of themselves","An event entirely unrelated to personal growth"], answer:2},
     {q:"Why is the bildungsroman considered a significant and enduring literary form?", options:["It captures a universal experience of growth and change that continues to resonate across generations","This literary form has no lasting significance","Coming-of-age narratives are rarely explored in literature","This genre has no connection to broader literary traditions"], answer:0}
