     {q:"Why is the skeletal system important beyond just supporting movement?", options:["It also protects internal organs and plays a role in processes like blood cell production","The skeletal system has no function beyond supporting movement","Bones have no connection to protecting internal organs","This system has no role in any bodily process besides movement"], answer:0},
     {q:"Why might understanding the muscular and skeletal systems be important for fields like physiotherapy?", options:["This knowledge has no practical, real-world application","Physiotherapy never involves an understanding of muscles or bones","These systems have no relevance to physiotherapy or injury treatment","It helps professionals diagnose and treat injuries or conditions affecting movement and structure"], answer:3}
