     {q:"Which is an example of a situation where understanding standard deviation would be useful?", options:["A situation where only the total sum of values matters","A situation with no connection to data analysis","A scenario that requires no interpretation of numerical data","Comparing the consistency of test scores between two different classes"], answer:3},
     {q:"Why might two data sets have the same mean but very different standard deviations?", options:["This situation could never occur in real data sets","The individual data values can be spread out very differently even if their average is the same","The mean and standard deviation are always identical for any two data sets","Standard deviation has no connection to how data values are distributed"], answer:1}
