     {q:"Why might radical functions be useful for modelling real-world situations, such as the relationship between an object’s speed and stopping distance?", options:["This concept only applies to purely abstract mathematics","They can represent relationships where one quantity depends on the root of another","Radical functions have no real-world modelling applications","This type of situation can never be represented mathematically"], answer:1}
