     {q:"Why might a population resulting from the founder effect have reduced genetic diversity compared to the original population?", options:["The founder effect always increases genetic diversity in a new population","Only a limited sample of the original population’s genetic variation is carried forward","This concept has no relevance to evolutionary biology","Genetic diversity has no connection to how a new population is established"], answer:1},
     {q:"Why are genetic drift and the founder effect important concepts for understanding evolutionary change?", options:["This topic has no relevance to studying biology","They illustrate how chance events, not just natural selection, can shape a population’s genetic makeup over time","Evolution occurs exclusively through natural selection, with no other contributing factors","These concepts have no connection to evolutionary change"], answer:1}
